        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Would things change if we tighten the requirements to always have a terminating `<` for codeblocks?\r\n\r\nBut it should be noted that tree-sitter-markdown also tried and failed and in the end had to switch to a two-pass strategy where one parser only parses the block structure, and a second parser does inline parsing of each individual block. (This works but has obvious performance implications.)",
