        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> tighten the requirements to always have a terminating `<` for codeblocks?\r\n\r\nInstead of \"always\", maybe _only_ if the next block is a h1 or column_heading? \r\n\r\nSo this would be allowed:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfoo >\r\n  code\r\nbar >\r\n  code\r\n<\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut this would _not_ be allowed:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfoo >\r\n  code\r\n\r\n=========\r\nh1\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis wouldn't result in a perfect AST but might be good enough.",
